plot.name: mature tall caatinga natural forest
variables.name: Biomass_root_total
notes: 50 cm x 50 cm monolith in each of 13 plots to ground water level, all root sizes; does not include all roots because water level is lower at other times of year.. prim ref: Klinge and Herrera 1983, Herrera and Jordan 1981.
citations.author: Klinge
citations.title: Phytomass structure of natural plant communities on spodosols in southern Venezuela: The tall Amazon Caatinga forest

plot.name: mature tall caatinga natural forest
variables.name: ANPP_litterfall_3
notes: Annual mean from a 3-yr measurement period; from 42 collectors sampled weekly for "fine litter" (not defined). prim ref: Klinge and Herrera 1983, Herrera and Jordan 1981.
citations.author: Clark
citations.title: NPP Tropical Forest: Consistent Worldwide Site Estimates, 1967-1999, R1. Dataset.

plot.name: mature tall caatinga natural forest
variables.name: ANPP_branch
notes: assume it is annual mean from 3 yr; also includes fruits, probably on fallen branches, based on the notation in the table. prim ref: Klinge and Herrera 1983, Herrera and Jordan 1981.
citations.author: Clark
citations.title: NPP Tropical Forest: Consistent Worldwide Site Estimates, 1967-1999, R1. Dataset.

plot.name: mature tall caatinga natural forest
variables.name: Biomass_ag
notes: trees and climbers >=1 cm dbh, plus all understory plants, complete harvest, in 13 plots, each 10 m x 10 m. prim ref: Klinge and Herrera 1983, Herrera and Jordan 1981.
citations.author: Klinge
citations.title: Phytomass structure of natural plant communities on spodosols in southern Venezuela: The tall Amazon Caatinga forest

plot.name: Colorado forest
variables.name: Biomass_ag
notes: Aboveground biomass (min. tree size not specified) for 1981, based on allometry and harvest of 17 trees 6.5-36.7 cm diameter; . prim ref: Weaver and Murphy 1990; Biotropica 22(1):69-82..
citations.author: Clark
citations.title: NPP Tropical Forest: Consistent Worldwide Site Estimates, 1967-1999, R1. Dataset.
